Note:  This is early development code.  Therefore it is still very, very ugly ;)

audio decodes the analog audio tracks (still very rough, no CX decoding yet!)

ldd takes the raw RF data signal (captured using cxadc) and converts it into a raw composite video signal.  

ntsc performs the time base conversion and produces a 1685x505 16-bit grayscale file with some sync edges removed

comb takes that and runs it through a 2d (for now) comb filter 

to run:  

./ld [file] [start] [length] > [file].ld 
./ntsc [file.ld] > [file].tbc 3> [file].atiming
./comb [file].tbc > [file].rgb

cat [file].atiming | ./audio [file] [start] - > file.pcm 

or (somewhat) pipelined:

./ld file.raw [start] [length] | ./ntsc - | ./comb - > file.rgb

to view ld-decode output: display -size 1685x505 -depth 16 gray:mb.tbc 
to view ntsc-decode output: display -size 1488x480 -depth 8 rgb:mb.rgb
use this command line to make it a .jpg:  convert -size 1488x480 -depth 8 rgb:ntscbar.rgb -resize 640x480\! ntscbar.jpg

To convert from .rgb to high quality .mp4:

avconv -f rawvideo -pix_fmt rgb24 -s 1488x480 -i file.rgb -qscale 3 -s 720x480 file.mp4

